  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mid-Term Evaluation of the Zambia Prevention, Care, and Treatment II Project (ZPCT II)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IBTCI conducted a mid-term evaluation of the Zambia Prevention, Care, and Treatment II Project (ZPCT II) on behalf of the USAID/Zambia Population, Health, and Nutrition Office. IBTCI sought to evaluate ZPCT IIs progress made toward improving public sector HIV/AIDS service delivery support in five provinces of Zambia, which included an assessment of the project design (conceptual framework). IBTCI designed an evaluation methodology that employed mixed methods, and included in-depth discussions in five outlying provinces  which include urban and rural districts  where the team interviewed staff from the National HIV/AIDS/STI/TB Council, central Ministry of Health (MOH), and the Ministry of Community Development, Maternal and Child Health, and conducted site visits to health centers and hospitals in each district that provide a number of different HIV/AIDS services. IBTCI drafted an evaluation report which provides recommendations for achieving the stated project objectives and sustainability of ZPCT II initiatives.</narrative>
  </description>
